text: @elizabethagan Praying. Good news is that COVID-19 does not pass through the placenta not through breast milk. Also It is not present in amniotic fluid & It does not pass from mother to fetus during pregnancy. Mom will have to take precaution after baby is born as it’s still passed by fluids
